tags: [[Path Expressions]]
title: Ancestor Scopes
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Once a profile iterates `days[*].activities[*]`, the "current record" is an activity object.  Activity-level fields are reachable as `{{name}}`, `{{duration}}`, etc.  But what about the day's `date` or the trip's `country`?  Those live one or two levels //above// the current record.

The `..` segment walks up one iteration scope:

|!Token                       |!Reaches                      |
|`{{name}}`                   |the current activity's name   |
|`{{../date}}`                |the day's date (one up)       |
|`{{../../trip-name}}`        |the trip name (two up, root)  |

Stack as many `..` as you have `[*]`s in `records`.  More than that is an error (`binding-parent-too-deep`).
